Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
update_partition(25.10)                                update_partition(25.10)

Name
       update_partition  -  Creates a new partitioned output that contains the
       optimised blocks and top

Syntax
       update_partition

       [-pinLocation]

       [-postECOSuffix <postECOSuffix>]

       {-flexIlmECO}

       {-goldenBlockDir <directory>}

       -flexIlmDir <directory>[-ecoDir <directory>]

       [-fullNetlistWithECODir <directory> -flexILMECODir <directory>]

       Creates a new partitioned output that contains the optimised blocks and
       top. It also performs ECO on the original  block.  The  ECO  output  is
       saved  as  new Innovus database in the partitioned block. The ECO would
       happen only on flexILM partitions and not the regular blocks.

Parameters
       -ecoDir<directory>
              Specifies the scratch directory  for  partitioning  and  running
              distributed ECO job after optimization.

       -flexIlmDir<directory>
              Specifies  the new partitioned output directory containing opti-
              mized blocks/top and ECO results.

       -flexIlmECO
              Performs ECO on FlexILM modules.

              Note: This is default.

       -flexILMECODir <directory>
              Specifies the postOpt FlexILM data directory.

       -fullNetlistWithECODir <directory>
              Specifies the directory to store full netllist ECO result.

       -goldenBlockDir <directory>
              Specifies the golden database directory for individual blocks.

       -pinLocation
              Updates new partition pin locations into the  golden  block  DB.
              This option does not allow new added logic ports.

       -postECOSuffix <postECOSuffix>
              Specifies the suffix name that will be part of generated postECO
              DB name.

Examples
       The  following  command  will  perform  ECO  on the block of tdsp_core,
       ram_128x16_test and ram_256x16_test.The ECO output is saved as new  In-
       novus  database  with the suffix "_postECO" at the "../flexILM_postOpt"
       directory (which is defined by the -flexIlmDir option) for each  speci-
       fied partition block.

       update_partition -flexIlmECO \

       -goldenBlockDir ../../PTN/tdsp_core/tdsp_core_data.enc.dat \

       -goldenBlockDir  ../../PTN/ram_128x16_test/ram_128x16_test_data.enc.dat
       \

       -goldenBlockDir  ../../PTN/ram_256x16_test/ram_256x16_test_data.enc.dat
       \

       -flexIlmDir ../flexIlm_postOpt -postECOSuffix postECO

       After update_partition, a new dir of flexIlm_postOpt will be generated.
       Under this directory, ecoDataSummary.rpt will be generated to show sum-
       mary  for  post  ECO data and an example for assembleDesign to use post
       ECO data.

       # Post ECO Data Summary

       ################################################################################

       TOP data: ../flexIlm_postOpt/dtmf_recvr_core

       ram_256x16_test                     data:                      ../flex-
       Ilm_postOpt/ram_256x16_test/ram_256x16_test_postECO.enc.dat

       ram_128x16_test                      data:                     ../flex-
       Ilm_postOpt/ram_128x16_test/ram_128x16_test_postECO.enc.dat

       tdsp_core data: ../flexIlm_postOpt/tdsp_core/tdsp_core_postECO.enc.dat

       ################################################################################

       #To assemble postECO full netlist data, please run

       assembleDesign -fe -topDir ../flexIlm_postOpt/dtmf_recvr_core\

        -blockDir                                                     ../flex-
       Ilm_postOpt/ram_256x16_test/ram_256x16_test_postECO.enc.dat\

        -blockDir                                                     ../flex-
       Ilm_postOpt/ram_128x16_test/ram_128x16_test_postECO.enc.dat\

        -blockDir ../flexIlm_postOpt/tdsp_core/tdsp_core_postECO.enc.dat\

        -mmmcFile <full chip viewDefinition file>

       ################################################################################

       Note: if there is no -postECOSuffix specified, a suffix of "eco_<system
       time>" will be added to the ECO database.

